22/01/2006
TIRANA, Albania -- The OSCE praised on Friday (20 January) the establishment of a special commission within the Albanian legislature that would deal with crucial electoral reform. 
In a joint statement, the OSCE Presence in Tirana and ODIHR welcomed the launch of the commission as a step forward in the process of improving the electoral process and bringing it into line with international standards.
In other news, Macedonian Prime Minister Vlado Buckovski kicks off a two-day working visit to Tirana on Monday. 
Aides say the focus will be issues related to bilateral co-operation and regional development. 
(Makfax - 21/01/06; OSCE Web site - 20/01/06)
